# web.php üö¶

Define routes in `routes/web.php`.

<!-- FULL_CODE_START
Route::get('/', function () {
    return view('welcome');
});

Route::get('/hello', function () {
    return 'Hello World';
});
FULL_CODE_END -->

# Dynamic Segments üÜî

<!-- FULL_CODE_START
Route::get('/user/{id}', function ($id) {
    return 'User '.$id;
});
FULL_CODE_END -->

You can also make them optional: `/user/{name?}`.

# Naming Things üè∑Ô∏è

Give routes a name to reference them easily later.

<!-- FULL_CODE_START
Route::get('/profile', function () {
    // ...
})->name('profile');

// Generating URL
$url = route('profile');
FULL_CODE_END -->

# Organizing üì¶

Group routes by prefix or middleware.

<!-- FULL_CODE_START
Route::prefix('admin')->group(function () {
    Route::get('/users', function () { ... });
    // Matches /admin/users
});
FULL_CODE_END -->
